           [1m--shell[0m
               This makes getmouselocation output shell data you can eval. Example:

                % xdotool getmouselocation --shell
                X=880
                Y=443
                SCREEN=0
                WINDOW=16777250

                % eval $(xdotool getmouselocation --shell)
